OL,3,CCalls for clarity over future of day
OL,4,Ccentres at risk of closure
OL,6,F"But staff and users of the day
OL,7,Fcentres are now panicking more than
OL,8,Fever ` they don't know why they
OL,9,Fhaven't had the same assurance.
OL,11,F"I've spoken to people who will have
OL,12,Fto put relatives into care homes if
OL,13,Fthe day centre shuts.
OL,15,F"I know a lady who works full time and
OL,16,Fwhose mother goes to Milbanke Day
OL,17,FCentre and she couldn't cope if she
OL,18,Flost access to that.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
